Comment: First age range cannot be ex-smoker; at this age about 3% are smokers; https://minhealthnz.shinyapps.io/nz-health-survey-2018-19-annual-data-explorer/_w_07361577/_w_6681b233/_w_022902a4/#!/explore-topics
rate for quitting starts at 0.1 at younger age but then goes up; https://truthinitiative.org/research-resources/quitting-smoking-vaping/what-you-need-know-quit-smoking
after 5 years, relapse rate is about 25%; https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3723776/
if they are older, they are more likely to have smoked;https://minhealthnz.shinyapps.io/nz-health-survey-2018-19-annual-data-explorer/_w_07361577/_w_6681b233/_w_022902a4/#!/explore-topics
Reduce chances of remaining a smoker the older someone gets
Reduce chances of going back to smoking the older someone gets
Increase the chances of someone remaining a non-smoker the older they get
At 20_24 much more young people are likely to be smokers
